main event: On 26 August 1958, in Lexington, Kentucky, a ground-visual observation of two cigar-shaped, copper-colored objects was reported. The objects were seen to vary in course and their presence was confirmed by photographs. The observation lasted approximately 30 minutes and was listed as insufficient data for a conclusive explanation.
interesting points: The objects were described as cigar-shaped, copper in color, and moving in varying courses, indicating controlled movement.
The witness reported seeing a humming sound approximately 3 minutes after the observation, suggesting a potential audio component to the event.
Photographs were taken to document the objects, indicating a level of visibility and detail to the sighting.
The estimated speed of the objects was reported as 6,000 m.p.h., suggesting extremely high velocities beyond conventional aircraft capabilities.
The witness had special educational training as a Naval Aviator, which implies expertise in identifying aerial phenomena.
sighted object: Two cigar-shaped, copper-colored objects in the sky
